<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Guidelines</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">STFC W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">STEM NETWORK </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">(WSC090) </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">STFC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">WiSTEM (Women in Science, Technology, Engineering and Maths) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">network of women working in science, technology, engineering and mathematics </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">at the Rutherford Appleton and Daresbury Laboratories (RAL and DL) run by the Science and Technology Facilities Council (STFC), </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">at </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">other institutional </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tenants </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">at the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Harwell a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nd Daresbury Science and Technology Campuses, such as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Diamond </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Light Source</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Nuvia Ltd, the Research Complex at Harwell</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Public Health England's Centre for Radiation, Chemical and Environmental Hazards</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A list of our </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Committee </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">members can be found in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Appendix 1.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">WiSTEM’s primary </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">aim is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to provide </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mutual support and encouragement </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to women working in STEM disciplines, in particular where there is a potential for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">female researchers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">find working in a historically or predominately male-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">dominated enviro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to be challenging</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. We </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">hold </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">regular</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">meetings</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> co-ordinate a li</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">v</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ely online discussion group</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, convene focus groups to address specific issues, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">arrange </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">networking lunche</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for our members to share experiences with others working in STEM and hear talks from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">speaker</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">internal or external, with a perspective on the subject of STEM careers for women.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The purpose of our submission is to highlight some examples of the challenges</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> WiSTEM has identified over its</span><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">9</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> years of operation which we hope maybe of interest to the Committee. We would welcome the opportunity to share some of these observations and answer questions in person </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">once the Committee holds oral hearings or conducts an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">y site visits.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt; padding-top:1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Why do numbers of women in STEM academic careers decline further up the career ladder?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Various studies offer reasons for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">gender differences </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in society as a whole</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and within STEM careers in particular. For example, it is proposed that both men and women may hold certain h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ypotheses, or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">gender schemas</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">with regard to their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">expect</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ations of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">professional and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">personal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">life, how they perform and how they are judged</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">It i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s difficult to deny that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STEM </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">being a male dominated field </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">has resulted in a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">male orientated </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">culture</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, perhaps still being </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">perpetuated by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e.g. the marketing of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">science toys </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">primarily to boys from an early age</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is potential </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">unconscious bias</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">en</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, plays a part in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">impeding </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">’s progress in STEM careers over the long term</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> despite the perception </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">success in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the scientific</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> arena is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">based on merit alone.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Without wanting to support any specific theory, WiSTEM members do report a number of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">factors related to gender perception which they believe ha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ve </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">had an impact on their own</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">colleagues’ </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and other women’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ability </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or desire </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to progress to the highest levels of careers within STEM. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">These </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">include:</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In contrast to other disciplines, STEM is per</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ceived as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">route to demonstrating personal achievement, rather than as an endeavour which improves peoples’ lives as a whole.</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Within </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">some </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STEM</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> fields (for example, chemistry, computational science, theoretical physics, etc.)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ndependent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> work </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tends to be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">valued more than collaborative work</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> which in turn tends to favour male </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">success factors</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. For example, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">U</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">niversities require</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> senior staff to establish and lead their own </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">independent </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">research </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">group</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s; individually</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">-authored publications </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are a major m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">easure of ability</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STEM careers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are often </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">portrayed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to be both </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">all-consuming</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and overwhelmingly competitive. There is a strong preconception that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">one cannot </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">participate in science on anything other than a completely immersive basis.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STEM careers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">characteristically </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">progress </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">according </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">prestige</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> built amongst peers, which is perceived to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be in contrast to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">preferred measures of success</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> favoured by women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STEM career progression focusses on q</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uantity </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">most important measure of productivity (e.g. number of publications, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">citations, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">H-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">index</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> which militates against career breaks or reduced working hours.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Evaluation of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">success </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in STEM jobs </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">typically </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">relies heavily on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">‘quantity’ (see above), </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">technical </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ability and intellectual rigor</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">but </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">often </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">fails to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">formally </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">highlight </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and recognise </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">facets of ability which have a significant impact on actual performance</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">For example, a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cademic scientists spend a considerable </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">proportion of their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">time communicating</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (in ar</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ticles, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">at conferences and seminars</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">), </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">networking, writing grant proposals, supervising students, managing staff, teaching and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">- </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">increasingly</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">performing public outreach activities and working </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the commercial exploitation of their findings. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Failure to re</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cognise </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the importance of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">these overarching activities potentially </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">reinforces </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">gender bias.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Studies such as the 2011 McKinsey Report</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> show that men have the advantage of being promoted based on their future potential, whereas women are promoted based on past performance. The factors above serve to demonstrate how this may be further accentuated within STEM and incrementally increase fur</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ther up the career ladder</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Studies also show that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for those women who are successful in male dominated fields, they are less liked and more personally derogated than equivalently successful men, and being disliked can have career-affecting outcomes</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">emb</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ers of the WISTEM network </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">report that they </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">have repeatedly heard women citing the following</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> reas</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ons for leaving STEM careers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> or lowering their expectations of career progression:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“I am</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> not good enough for STEM”.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> come to believe tha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t they do not hav</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e the talent, skills,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> or motivation r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">equired to advance in a STEM career. They perceive their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">male </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">peers as better prepared or more motivated than they are.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">STEM is not for me”.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> perceive that STEM career</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> do</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">not play to their strengths or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">motivations.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“In order to succeed in STEM, one has to sacrific</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">e relationships and family”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ear that a career in STEM can</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">not be reconciled with their (future) domestic life. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In contrast, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">iSTEM members are keen to emphasise </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">their own experiences</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> differ and a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n academic STEM job </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">often </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">offers greater flexibility than a teaching job</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> when it comes to raising </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a family</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“A STEM career</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> requires too much commitment and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">too many </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">sacrifices for a job with little stability in the early stages and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">relatively low </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">financial returns.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The short term nature and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">need to be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">high</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ly</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> geographical</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ly mobile, particularly during </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">early</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">career</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, is a major </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">obstacle highlighted by women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, especially when contrasted with the financial rewards and stability other care</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ers with such deman</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s can bring in the long term.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt; padding-top:1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">When women leave academia, what careers do they transition into? What are the consequences of scientifically trained women applying their skills in different employment sectors?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Members of WiS</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">TEM have witnessed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">many women leave </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STEM research </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">career</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">school </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">teaching. Somewhat less frequently, there is a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">transition </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">other skilled numerate or technical careers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e.g. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">scientists in industry, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">patent attorneys, IT managers, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">project managers,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or job</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in the financial and banking sector. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A significant proportion may move away fro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> frontline research but continue to work in STEM support roles. For example, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STFC employs many women who have left academia to transition to science </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">support work </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">g. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">programme management, communication, public engagement and business development</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> - in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> fact in several of these areas there is an overwhelming </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">majority of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">female staff.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Whilst</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> on the whole</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t is positive that a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">reas outside STEM benefit from the skills </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and perspectives of highly STEM qualified individuals, it does appear that such transition</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">more likely for women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> than </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">men. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Not only does this lead to a reduction in the degree of gender diversity within STEM</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, but it would also appear to show that a lower proportion of women are fully exploiting their potential within STEM despite </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">high degree of training to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ost-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">octoral level and beyond. There is some evidence to show that, where women do stay within STEM, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">they may choose to work in areas that are away from the front line of research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and below, for example, their realistic earning capacity</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The representation of women among STEM undergraduates in the UK is increasing. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">WiSTEM believe it is important that, now this trend is established, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that the “leaky pipeline” is mended so that STEM does not face a worsening skills shortage in the future.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt; padding-top:1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">What should universities and the higher education sector do to retain women grad</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uates and PhD students in academic careers? Are there examples of good practice?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As a group with a wide range of experiences of working in STEM, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">WiSTEM </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">make the following </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">suggestions </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for activities which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">may help u</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">niversities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">higher education </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sector </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">more effectively </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">retain women graduates and PhD students:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Raise </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">general </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">awareness </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that STEM has historically been a male dominated field and that both women and men need to work towards reducing any continuing in-built bias. This might include awar</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eness</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">raising for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">staff</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> at all levels within STEM organisations, as well as targeted training for individuals involved </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">recruiting and developing staff.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. It may be appropriate for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">peer-review processes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to be reviewed such that any </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">unconscious bias</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in ass</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">essments can be removed from processes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">procedures</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Instigate dialog</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ue</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> about the STEM culture and diversity and equality issues by holding high visi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">bility lectures followed by</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> discussions. An example of good practice comes from the South African Institute of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Physics which always includes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in its annual conference a plenary lecture on Women in Physics (this year given by a member of our network).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">PhD supervisors, university tuto</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rs and people managing STEM personnel should be trained to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">take</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> into account gender differences</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, for instance the Royal Society of Chemistry reports that female chemistry </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">PhDs </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">find the experience to be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">too isolating</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Funding bodies should </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">require diversi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ty </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">training </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">on the part of its grant recipients, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as well as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">training </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of their own staff managing grant applications.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">When </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sponsoring</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> conferences and other networking events, funding bodies should state that the list of invited speakers is expected to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">comprise both men and women, and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">justification </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is required </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">when </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a suitable degree of diversity is not demonstrated.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Funding bodies should also review the limitations on number of years since PhD for eligibility for some fellowships. This criterion sho</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uld be revised to take career breaks into account. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">For the latter point</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, an example of such good practice comes from the London Mathematical Society. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">PhD co</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">urses should include training on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> skills necessary for career advancement such as writing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">effective </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">grant proposals</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and successful </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">networking</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> activities, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as well </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as awareness</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">raising with regard to gender </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">bias.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Senior management and leaders of STEM organisations </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">should </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">endeavour to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">discourage </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">long-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">working-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">hours culture and promote </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">positive </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ork/life balance for all staff. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">lexible working</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> arrangements for both men and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women should be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">promoted wherever </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">it </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">can be seen to have no </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">negative</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> impact on productivity. In general, job descriptions </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">should be created that can be easily divided into part-time </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">chunks</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that can be shared among several people. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Ideally, there should be an aspiration for m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eetings </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be only held during core hours </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of the day, e.g. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">between 9:30 and 3pm</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and attendance </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">at </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mee</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tings (especially if international) via videolink should be routinely enabled whenever possible.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11.8.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Senior management and leaders of STEM organisations should endeavour to r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ecognise that both women and men have responsibilities outside of work and make reaso</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nable allowances </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">equally for both genders</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">when this</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> does not impact negatively on productivity</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> over the medium timescale</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Initiatives should encourage </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">equality of caring duties.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> For example, encourage male employees to take their turn picking their childre</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n up from school and take</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> time off when a child is sick</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> - t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">oo many schemes, such as flexible and part time working, seem to be aimed at helping women juggle and cope, but still assume that the women do more than their share of the domestic and caring </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">duties. Where possible, allow both men and women to work part time on a temporary basis if there is a problem in the family, wi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">thout losing full-time status. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Employers should recognise the increasing need for long term care of elderly relatives will be a s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ignificant trend over the coming years and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">recognise the need for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">gender equality </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">among</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> carers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11.9.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Quantitative measures of staff and job applicants’ productivity such as number of papers published and h-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">index</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> should be replaced </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">with a comprehensive evaluati</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">on of the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> person’s contribution to the organi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ation </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and the field</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">For example, they should provide </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">acknowledgement and credit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for tasks such as organisation of group seminars, engagement with visiting school-children, mentoring junior colleagues, taking </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">placement students, acting as counsellors, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to name just a few.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11.10.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STEM professions should be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">more effectively </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">marketed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">both genders. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Whilst leading edge STEM is clearly driven by tackling </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">very difficult intellectual challenges</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, this does not mean that success is founded solely on playing on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">personal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ambition and individual recognition, which some of our members feel to be the case.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">An alternative approach might be to better emphasise STEM’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">role in bringing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> change</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ociety, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">help</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> solve </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">g</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">lobal problems and mak</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> people’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">l</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ives better through collaborative working and co-operation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11.11.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">With regard to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">recruitment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">hen preparing adverts for vacancies, the advert content and language used should appeal to both genders</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In promo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tion and internal recruitment procedures, all eligible candidates should be actively encouraged to apply. This </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sh</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ould </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">help </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">compens</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ate for the tendency of women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> not </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">put themselves</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">forward</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> which some of our members have witnessed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">It is the experience of many women in our network that ambition is not considered a trait that women should display or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">admit to</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11.12.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Peer-reviewed STEM journals should not communicate the manuscript’s author’s names to the reviewers.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11.13.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In order to counteract the lack of job stability, the employment structure of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">many </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">research groups should be modified. At the moment these consist of one group leader with a permanent position and a number of postdoctoral research associates (referred to a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s postdocs) on fixed term contracts, in addition to PhD students. We propose that the role of senior postdocs should be professionalized by the creation of the permanent role of “researcher” to be associated with groups. This is the structure of research g</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">roups in other Countries such as Italy where the retention of women in STEM careers is much higher.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In 2011, STFC was awarded </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">SET Fair Standard</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and WiSTEM believe the basic principles upon which STFC was recognised and its other activities in this area are all examples of good practice for other HEIs and Universities, including:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:15.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Excellent range of flexible working arrangements - e.g., part time </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">work, school term time work, job share, flexible working hours</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, taken up by men as well as women</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:15.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Excellent maternity provision</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, and sharing of maternity leave between parents</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:15.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">On site nurseries</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:15.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Child care vouchers</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:15.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Support of the WiSTEM network</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:15.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Support of Wo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">men in Science Focus Group (an external group that includes representatives from HEIs and discusses access to grant funding)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:15.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Provision of the Women as Leaders programme run by Cranfield University</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:15.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Provision of Springboard programme</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:15.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Mentoring scheme</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:15.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Careers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> for Women brochure</span><a name="_ftnref9"></a><a href="#_ftn9">[9]</a></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:15.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Case studies of Women role models on STFC website</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:15.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Support of m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ajor conference</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> on Barriers for Women in STEM </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e.g. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">March 2012</span></li></ul></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Despite the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STFC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">initiatives</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, the percentage of women in STEM job</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in STFC stubbornly hovers around 11</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> per cent, highlighting the continuing need for new activities, initiatives and proposals.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt; padding-top:1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">What role should the Government have in encouraging the retention of women in academic STEM careers?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As a group with a wide range of experiences of working in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STEM, WiSTEM make the following suggestions for activities that the Government might undertake</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">14.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Require </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that universities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and other employers of STEM staff </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">choose and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">set</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> organi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ational </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">targets on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">numbers of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women at the different career stage</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and on equ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">al pay</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. These targets should be made public, together with data on the number of women and pay reviews.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">14.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">reate a national mentoring scheme where women at all career stages are paired with a women or man in a more advance</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> career</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">stage</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">14.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">O</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ffer a career advi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sing service to al</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">l PhD students which</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> addresses</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the issues of work/life balance</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, including real life testimonials.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">14.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">O</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ffer starter grants specifically aimed at early career women researchers in STEM, and grants for students and post-docs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">regardless of gender, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">returning after a career break.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">14.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Our political leaders should engage in a conversation with the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ation about gender issues, in particular on the social and economic advantages of sharing work, domestic commitments, and caring responsi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">bilities (for children, the disabled and the elderly) more equally between men and women. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">14.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Equalise the rights of women and men with respect to parental leave and make sure that the ratio between pay and childcare costs always makes it more advantageous f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or both parents to work.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">14.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Liaise with other governments, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the EU and organisations such as the World Economic Forum, which lists the gender issue as one of the key issues to tackle in order to improve the state of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">orld.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">14.8.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Encourage </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the Research Councils</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and other funding bodies to support </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">interdisciplinary research on women in STEM</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, the STEM culture,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and to gather statistics and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">data especially aimed at quantifying the effects of gender bias in STEM jobs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusion</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">WiSTEM welcomes the Committee’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nquiry and hopes that it will find this submission of interest with regard to our own experiences working </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">at the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">UK’s National </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Science and Innovation Campuses.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> We would be delighted to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> provide further information as the Inquiry progresses.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">APPENDIX 1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> –</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> ST</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">FC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> WiSTEM</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> Membership</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Committee</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Rom